                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="legend-body" value="• New VMs deploy on Azure Local cluster NTUA-OPS-HCI1-C, RG rg-AzureLocal-GIS_Production, domain ntua-ops.local.&#xa;• Base ArcGIS Enterprise multi-machine deployment per the ESRI reference architecture.&#xa;• Naming convention (Lee, 2026-06-05): ops2- prefix (gen-2 infra) + ESRI role.&#xa;• Internal tier (4 VMs) sits on the existing server VLAN at 10.23.62.130, .132, .134 plus one more (.133) TBD; .131 reserved as spare.&#xa;• DMZ tier (2 Web Adapter VMs) sits on a separate subnet behind Lee&#39;s Palo Alto NGFW. IP range TBD — confirming with Lee next week whether a DMZ already exists in his firewall config or needs to be built.&#xa;&#xa;Open questions for next sync with Lee:&#xa; 1. Does a DMZ already exist on the Palo Alto for this purpose, or do we design one (subnet + VLAN + rules)?&#xa; 2. Role / hostname for the 4th internal VM at .133.&#xa; 3. Disposition of GIS2APP1 / GIS6APP1 (originally assumed in scope, but Lee&#39;s edits point to the DEUCES stack instead).&#xa; 4. Sanity-check ops2- prefix against current AMI server naming to stay aligned." style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=11;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="90" y="880" width="680" height="170" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
